How come you guys are hostile again after a night together?

91
00:08:18,540 --> 00:08:20,360
It's worse than just being hostile.

92
00:08:20,360 --> 00:08:23,660
Your miss got divorced by the general!

93
00:08:23,660 --> 00:08:29,030
Miss, did you then become an abandoned wife?

94
00:08:29,030 --> 00:08:31,820
I'm not someone he can divorce so easily.

95
00:08:31,820 --> 00:08:33,680
I was betrothed to him by the royal decree.

96
00:08:33,680 --> 00:08:38,390
Now that he's hiding in the barracks, I'm not leaving the matter at that.

97
00:08:38,390 --> 00:08:40,820
I will wait at the general's manor. I can't believe he won't come back!

98
00:08:40,820 --> 00:08:42,960
What if he doesn't come back?

99
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:44,270
Then I'll go to the barracks.

100
00:08:44,270 --> 00:08:46,520
I must find out why he's divorcing me!

101
00:08:46,520 --> 00:08:50,070
Then what if he doesn't let you in the barracks?

102
00:08:51,730 --> 00:08:53,470
Rou Rou that's a good point.

103
00:08:53,470 --> 00:08:56,230
I need to think of another way to get into the barracks.

104
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:05,500
General, the new soldiers arrived.

105
00:09:44,770 --> 00:09:46,850
The third guy! Get in a straight line!

106
00:09:47,700 --> 00:09:51,310
I'm telling you to get in a straight line. Don't you understand—

107
00:10:05,650 --> 00:10:07,190
You!

108
00:10:07,190 --> 00:10:09,030
Why are you here?

109
00:10:12,900 --> 00:10:15,310
Reporting to the general, I'm your new soldier.

110
00:10:15,310 --> 00:10:17,030
Nonsense!

111
00:10:19,470 --> 00:10:23,830
I'm a new soldier recruit according to General's military draft notice.

112
00:10:23,830 --> 00:10:26,470
Those I want to draft are men to protect our homes and country!

113
00:10:26,470 --> 00:10:28,040
That's right!

114
00:10:28,040 --> 00:10:32,100
I also want to learn from General to have great aspirations and shoulder great responsibilities!

115
00:10:33,240 --> 00:10:35,060
<i>A man should have great aspirations.</i>

116
00:10:35,060 --> 00:10:39,730
<i>What's more, just as you said, heavy responsibilities lies on my shoulders—</i>

117
00:10:39,730 --> 00:10:43,660
Moreover, on the draft notice, it wasn't specified new soldiers should be men or women.

118
00:10:43,660 --> 00:10:45,720
Nor male or female.

119
00:10:45,720 --> 00:10:47,930
General never goes back on his words.

120
00:10:48,800 --> 00:10:50,510
<i>Are you really divorcing me?</i>

121
00:10:50,510 --> 00:10:52,850
<i>I never go back on my words.</i>

122
00:10:58,310 --> 00:11:00,200
I match all of the criterias.

123
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:02,420
How could the general go back on his promise?

124
00:11:03,790 --> 00:11:05,760
Fine!

125
00:11:05,760 --> 00:11:07,370
Let's not discuss the rest.

126
00:11:07,370 --> 00:11:12,750
You must know to become my soldiers, you have to pass the tests!

127
00:11:14,200 --> 00:11:15,910
As you command.

128
00:11:15,910 --> 00:11:19,630
Mountains of daggers and seas of flames. Dragon's pool and tiger's den. Please, bring it on!

129
00:13:14,240 --> 00:13:16,720
You! Come here!

130
00:13:17,930 --> 00:13:19,780
Yes, you!

131
00:13:47,860 --> 00:13:49,430
Begin!

132
00:13:55,590 --> 00:13:57,200
You win.

133
00:14:12,530 --> 00:14:14,980
You! Come forward!

134
00:14:19,500 --> 00:14:21,220
That was too fake just now!

135
00:14:21,220 --> 00:14:24,060
-Which part are you referring to, my Lady?
-All of them!

136
00:14:24,060 --> 00:14:26,840
That sandbag looks so heavy, but it's actually filled with cotton!

137
00:14:26,840 --> 00:14:28,460
Do you think everyone are fools?

138
00:14:28,460 --> 00:14:30,720
Also, just now up there!

139
00:14:30,720 --> 00:14:33,010
I hadn't even moved, but you already dodged!

140
00:14:33,010 --> 00:14:34,680
Can't you at least take two of my attacks?

141
00:14:34,680 --> 00:14:37,210
Lady, I can't even take half an attack from you, much less two.

142
00:14:37,210 --> 00:14:40,420
If I injure you even a little, I'd be dead.

143
00:14:40,420 --> 00:14:42,490
Please spare me.

144
00:14:44,140 --> 00:14:45,730
That's right! Where's Chu Xiuming?

145
00:14:45,730 --> 00:14:47,520
It's "General!"

146
00:14:47,520 --> 00:14:49,880
Cut the crap! Tell me!

147
00:14:56,670 --> 00:14:58,630
No more next time.

148
00:15:26,460 --> 00:15:29,360
Do you all understand? Practice now!

149
00:15:29,360 --> 00:15:30,690
-Yes!
-Yes!

150
00:15:42,150 --> 00:15:43,940
<i>Are you okay?</i>

151
00:15:59,690 --> 00:16:01,650
Are you okay?

152
00:16:04,840 --> 00:16:06,420
You!

153
00:16:06,420 --> 00:16:09,310
Yes, you! Come here!

154
00:16:16,180 --> 00:16:18,020
Slowly.

155
00:16:18,020 --> 00:16:20,870
I was practicing just fine. What are you doing?

156
00:16:20,870 --> 00:16:24,720
This item is too dangerous. I'm afraid you'll hurt someone.

157
00:16:24,720 --> 00:16:27,540
Everyone is practicing the same! What are you talking about?

158
00:16:27,540 --> 00:16:30,210
You are a girl! You are my-!

159
00:16:30,210 --> 00:16:31,860
What?

160
00:16:34,680 --> 00:16:36,440
You're my soldier.

161
00:16:36,440 --> 00:16:39,940
My soldier must listen to my orders.

162
00:16:40,870 --> 00:16:43,100
Fine, fine. I'll be careful.

163
00:16:43,100 --> 00:16:45,510
You done talking? I'm going to practice.

164
00:16:45,510 --> 00:16:47,050
Stop!

165
00:16:49,920 --> 00:16:51,710
I'll practice with you.

166
00:16:55,980 --> 00:16:57,580
Okay!

167
00:17:16,880 --> 00:17:19,560
How interesting, General! You keep avoiding her.

168
00:17:19,560 --> 00:17:21,600
It'll be hard to win!

169
00:17:25,660 --> 00:17:28,810
If you keep running, I won't hold back!

170
00:17:31,990 --> 00:17:33,970
Hurry and stop! Don't hurt yourself!

171
00:17:33,970 --> 00:17:36,140
Cut the crap! Watch this!

172
00:17:47,530 --> 00:17:50,400
General, I've won. Thanks.

173
00:17:50,400 --> 00:17:53,160
Um...be careful, General.

174
00:17:53,160 --> 00:17:55,140
Don't catch a cold!

175
00:18:00,270 --> 00:18:02,890
How amazing! She beat the General!

176
00:18:02,890 --> 00:18:05,010
That was rather talented.

177
00:18:05,760 --> 00:18:07,390
<i>She's not bad.</i>

178
00:18:07,390 --> 00:18:09,110
That's really amazing.

179
00:18:09,110 --> 00:18:11,280
Pretty good!

180
00:18:12,950 --> 00:18:15,430
Let's continue. Come.

181
00:18:28,570 --> 00:18:31,440
It seems like this arranged marriage worked very well.

182
00:18:31,440 --> 00:18:35,010
I hope General can watch over the borders properly for me.

183
00:18:35,010 --> 00:18:40,710
Your Majesty, on this trip, I heard some...rumors.

184
00:18:40,710 --> 00:18:42,410
Oh?

185
00:18:44,900 --> 00:18:46,890
Let's hear it.

186
00:18:48,520 --> 00:18:53,090
It seems like...General has a spy in court.

187
00:18:53,090 --> 00:18:55,090
Where did this news come from?

188
00:18:55,090 --> 00:18:57,290
I'm not sure about the details.

189
00:18:57,290 --> 00:19:02,930
However, General Chu has a good news source. He is aware of all of your actions.

190
00:19:04,880 --> 00:19:07,930
Cut off the transfer station that send things to the General's Manor.

191
00:19:07,930 --> 00:19:10,230
Investigate this thoroughly.

192
00:19:10,230 --> 00:19:11,900
Is Xiao Su in the city?

193
00:19:11,900 --> 00:19:15,100
He is. You want to summon him?

194
00:19:15,100 --> 00:19:16,440
Have him await my orders.

195
00:19:16,440 --> 00:19:17,870
Yes.

196
00:19:19,100 --> 00:19:21,030
I will take my leave.

197
00:19:37,850 --> 00:19:39,610
This is from Lord Liu.

198
00:19:39,610 --> 00:19:42,000
You've worked hard.

199
00:19:49,580 --> 00:19:52,800
<i>Kites!</i>

200
00:20:00,850 --> 00:20:02,880
Candied fruit!

201
00:20:05,330 --> 00:20:07,200
<i>Candied hawthorns!</i>

202
00:20:13,770 --> 00:20:16,810
Yearning, yearning.

203
00:20:16,810 --> 00:20:19,520
If one's asking when the yearning ends,

204
00:20:19,520 --> 00:20:22,990
whenever else than once we meet?

205
00:20:30,810 --> 00:20:33,710
Brother, let me ask you about someone. Do you know Lord Jin?

206
00:20:33,710 --> 00:20:35,340
I don't.

207
00:20:40,730 --> 00:20:41,980
<i>[Travellers' Pavilion Hall]</i>

208
00:20:41,980 --> 00:20:44,380
Madam, let me ask you about someone.

209
00:20:44,380 --> 00:20:46,050
Do you know of Lord Jin?

210
00:20:46,050 --> 00:20:48,320
I'm sorry, I don't.

211
00:20:48,320 --> 00:20:49,470
It's okay.

212
00:20:49,470 --> 00:20:51,530
Come come come. Take a look!

213
00:20:51,530 --> 00:20:53,360
Young Master, take a look!

214
00:20:53,360 --> 00:20:56,160
- Extremely good porcelain. Buy one!
- I want to ask about someone.

215
00:20:56,160 --> 00:20:57,610
Please give me some money.

216
00:20:57,610 --> 00:20:59,150
Thank you.

217
00:21:00,450 --> 00:21:03,510
My Lord! My Lord! Give us some money!

218
00:21:03,510 --> 00:21:05,650
Give us some money, My Lord!

219
00:21:05,650 --> 00:21:08,170
My Lord!

220
00:21:08,170 --> 00:21:10,320
Thank you! Thank you My Lord!

221
00:21:10,320 --> 00:21:13,350
-You all want some?
-Yes!

222
00:21:13,350 --> 00:21:16,020
Alright. Let me ask you about someone.

223
00:21:16,020 --> 00:21:19,260
-My Lord, who are you looking for?
-Who are you looking for?

224
00:21:19,260 --> 00:21:22,490
In the past, there was a person on this street called Lord Jin.

225
00:21:22,490 --> 00:21:26,560
-Oh! Lord Jin! I know, I know!
-I know!

226
00:21:29,190 --> 00:21:32,020
I was so thirsty after beating the General! Thanks!

227
00:21:32,020 --> 00:21:35,250
My Lady, we have to face the possibility of an ambush every day.

228
00:21:35,250 --> 00:21:37,340
We might lose our lives here.

229
00:21:37,340 --> 00:21:39,130
The General is busy with military affairs.

230
00:21:39,130 --> 00:21:42,090
He has to maintain the army and defend against the Falcon Tribe.

231
00:21:42,090 --> 00:21:45,610
His mind has been wandering recently.

232
00:21:45,610 --> 00:21:48,120
He's worried about your safety.

233
00:21:49,190 --> 00:21:52,050
I...know he's busy.

234
00:21:52,050 --> 00:21:55,040
I came to help share his burden.

235
00:21:55,040 --> 00:21:57,330
Besides, who told him to—

236
00:21:58,050 --> 00:22:00,650
do something that made me angry?

237
00:22:01,550 --> 00:22:03,890
General has spent many years guarding the border on his own.

238
00:22:03,890 --> 00:22:07,990
He is a quiet man who hides his emotions in his heart.

239
00:22:07,990 --> 00:22:11,290
He has to protect the royal court and millions of citizens.

240
00:22:11,290 --> 00:22:14,720
If he was in a bad mood and offended you,

241
00:22:14,720 --> 00:22:16,510
I hope you will be understanding!

242
00:22:16,510 --> 00:22:18,680
That's not what I mean.

243
00:22:20,300 --> 00:22:22,980
I understand what you mean, Deputy General.

244
00:22:23,680 --> 00:22:25,350
Thank you, my Lady!

245
00:22:46,350 --> 00:22:49,170
General. I just received news.

246
00:22:49,170 --> 00:22:53,710
The Emperor has ordered the transfer stations to hold everything coming and going from the General's manor.

247
00:22:55,260 --> 00:22:57,620
Including letters from Rui Manor?

248
00:22:57,620 --> 00:22:59,260
Yes.

249
00:23:04,320 --> 00:23:08,070
Have someone watch the Lady, and add guards around the camp.

250
00:23:08,080 --> 00:23:10,050
Yes, I will follow your order.

251
00:23:15,380 --> 00:23:18,360
<i>No one knows about this besides me and her.</i>

252
00:23:18,360 --> 00:23:21,320
